The Kiess route-dispatch office requires an updated threat assessment of the Mirror Flats crossing routes before certifying the next Reach transit season. Salt cricket swarm leaders occupy the cricket breeding grounds north of the Swift Line, cairn kite alphas have claimed elevated survey points along Crystal Ridge, and corrupted Warden toll-thieves are interfering with caravan data collection at approach checkpoints. Engage one of each and return field observations to the postmaster.
The Mirror Flats survey data has been incorporated into the updated Reach cartographic record on file with Kiess route-dispatch. Cricket swarm pressure along the northern Swift Line and kite territory at Crystal Ridge are now properly documented, and the interference from corrupted toll-thieves at the approach checkpoints has been cleared. The postmaster has issued updated crossing advisories to all certified caravan operators.

